Well, the &quot;discussion&quot; of Pattern glass seems to be in need of a boost! I was
wondering after reading the recent posts on guide prices, what pattern glass
collectors seemed to think about price guides. In particular I've noticed a
trend here in Texas and I wonder if the same thing happens in other places.
What seems to happen around here is that if a dealer identifies a piece of
glass correctly it gets priced well above &quot;guide&quot; price regardless of
condition, or rarity. Unidentified or mis identified pieces are generally
available under guide price. For instance I bought an AUSTRIAN pattern 8in vase
this weekend that was only labelled old pattern glass goblet for about 25% of
the price listed by Measel in his Greentown Glass book. I'm convinced that if
this dealer had known what he had it would have been priced at twice the guide
price. Has anyone else encountered this recently?
-Norm

